# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PR Website — Environment
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is a fully STATIC site (served from /public, no build step,
# no Node/server runtime). Nothing reads a .env at runtime, so this
# file does NOT need to be filled in to run or deploy the site.
#
# The only backend is Supabase. Its config lives directly in the
# client (public/journal.html):
#   - Project URL
#   - anon (public) key  ← safe to expose in the browser; access is
#                          restricted by Row Level Security (RLS).
#
# This file is kept only as a reference for the values used, in case
# a build step is added later. The anon key is already public (it
# ships in journal.html); NEVER put the Supabase service_role key or
# any private secret here or anywhere in client-side code.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase (public — currently set client-side in public/journal.html)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_public_key
